inference:
The largest prime factor of 2323 is 71.

2323 % 2 = 1 (not divisible by 2)
2323 % 3 = 2 (not divisible by 3)
2323 % 5 = 3 (not divisible by 5)
2323 % 7 = 0 (divisible by 7)
2323 / 7 = 331

331 % 2 = 1 (not divisible by 2)
331 % 3 = 1 (not divisible by 3)
331 % 5 = 1 (not divisible by 5)
331 % 7 = 0 (divisible by 7)
331 / 7 = 47

47 % 2 = 1 (not divisible by 2)
47 % 3 = 1 (not divisible by 3)
47 % 5 = 2 (not divisible by 5)
47 % 7 = 0 (divisible by 7)
47 / 7 = 7

7 is a prime number and it is a factor of 2323.

Hence, the largest prime factor of 2323 is \\boxed{$7$}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: Find the prime factorization of 2323: $2323=23\cdot101$. The largest prime factor of 2323 is $\boxed{101}$.
